05_chapter03_synopsis_01

After escaping the mining pit and a long journey, Reisha and
Akane finally arrived at the royal capital, Near Lake. What
greeted them upon their return was the sight of soldiers and
citizens busily scurrying about, preparing for a military
march.

The atmosphere, as if being hurried by an invisible hand to
deploy, was enough to give them a premonition that they were
entering into some exceptional situation.
05_chapter03_synopsis_02

However, what awaited them at the gates was an order from
the chancellor stating, "During the military preparations
within the royal capital, entry is currently forbidden to
all."
05_chapter03_synopsis_03

Unable to get a message through to anyone they knew and with
no other recourse, the two were turned away by the gate
guards. Then, they heard an ominous rumor: "The current
expedition preparations are not for subjugating a monster's
nest but for preparations to wage war against a neighboring
country."

Could they somehow glean any insight into the tightly sealed
and heavily guarded situation within the royal capital?
Desiring even a sliver of information, Reisha looked
troubled, prompting Akane to suggest, "If you want
information, I know just the place."
05_chapter03_synopsis_04

They were led to what is known as the "Reconstruction
District," located on the edge of the royal capital's
territory, also called "Twilight's Resting Place." Reisha
observed the residents of this area living robustly amidst
diversity.
05_chapter03_synopsis_05

Caught off guard by the different atmosphere from Near Lake,
the central district of the royal capital, Reisha was led by
Akane into a certain building where once again, the stage
was set for their story to unfold──.

After escaping from the mining pit and enduring a long

Upon their return, they witnessed soldiers and citizens
hurriedly running around, busy with preparations for a
military march.

The atmosphere was peculiar, as if they were being rushed to
deploy, which was enough to make them feel that they were
entering into some exceptional situation.
What do you mean we can't pass through...!!

Gate Guard: The royal capital is currently under strict
vigilance due to preparations for deployment.

Gate Guard: By order, we cannot allow anyone to pass
through. I'm sorry, but no matter what you say, we cannot
let you into the royal capital at this time.

I'm not asking you to let us through by force. I admire your
dedication to fulfilling your duties as a mercenary summoned
from various places.

All I ask is that you send a messenger to the castle saying
"Knight Reisha has returned." At least let me meet someone
from the castle who knows me. That should clear up our
situation.
Gate Guard: Then all the more reason I cannot let you pass.
What did you say!?

Gate Guard: We have been strictly warned by the chancellor
to be especially wary of anyone who claims to be a knight
and shows signs of communicating with the castle.
The chancellor has... What does this mean...?

Gate Guard: Due to preparations for deployment, a variety of
supplies and people are currently flooding into the royal
capital. Opportunistic thieves may take advantage of this
chaos. It's likely an attempt to avoid unnecessary trouble.

Gate Guard: I understand it's an inconvenience, but I must
ask you to leave for today.
Damn it...! What in the world is going on!!

We can't pass through, that's absurd! Besides, the plan for
subjugating monsters in the west wasn't supposed to happen
yet. Why such elaborate preparations...!!
